HEADWORD: Anthobranchia
<hw>An`tho*bran"chi*a</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>'a`nqos</grk> flower + <?/ gills, n. pl.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of nudibranchiate Mollusca, in which
the gills form a wreath or cluster upon the posterior part of the back.
See <er>Nudibranchiata</er>, and <er>Doris</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anthocarpous</ent>⟦br⟧
